        "state": "engineered",
        "edbb": {
          "role": "trading",
          "intro": "A minimalist starter trade fit. Initial is buy-only; A-rated is the trade baseline; Engineered is rarely worth it on a starter, but maximises range if you wish.",
          "callout": {
            "label": "Cargo and a token shield",
            "text": "Fill the tiny optionals with cargo racks and a small shield. The Hauler can't really defend itself, so trade in safe systems while you learn — the shield buys seconds to submit-and-flee an interdiction with your goods."
          },
          "notes": {
            "TinyHardpoint1": "Heavy Duty multiplies raw shield strength.",
            "TinyHardpoint2": "Optional / low-priority — Ammo Capacity adds heat-sink charges. Dumps heat for silent running and Thermal-Vent resets.",
            "PowerPlant": "A-rate to power the shield and modules; Low Emissions keeps heat and signature down so you draw less attention.",
            "MainEngines": "A-rate the thrusters so a laden hull can boost away from an interdiction; Clean Drive Tuning adds speed without the heat.",
            "FrameShiftDrive": "A-rate first — range is the Hauler's one real strength; Increased Range with Mass Manager stretches every laden jump between markets.",
            "LifeSupport": "D-rate to save mass and credits; Lightweight trims more, and life support has no experimental effect.",
            "PowerDistributor": "Charge Enhanced raises the weapon, engine and system capacitors.",
            "Radar": "D-rate and go Lightweight; a trader needs no sensor range, so save the mass for jump range.",
            "FuelTank": "Stock class-2 tank; fuel capacity is fixed and cannot be engineered.",
            "Slot01_Size3": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
            "Slot02_Size3": "Optional — Expanded Capacity adds cargo space; worth it for dedicated haulers. Holds cargo.",
